<br>
Speaking as a SK ... my pet serves ONE function.  To die.  He is there ONLY do die as a VERY short term Pet mez.  He does add a little DPS when buffed, but with a good group, his contribution is nearly negligible.  ALL he does is takes about 5 or 6 hits to give me a few moments to do whatever I am going to do.<br>
<br>
NOW ...<br>
MOST SKs don't even USE their pets. I only got into the habit of using mine because I had to solo so damn much when I started my SK and was too stupid a noob to start a necro.  At this point, Tib is high enough that his pet is worth considering .. but not as much more than a glorified DoT that doesn't take much manna.<br>
<br>
Mage toys ... sure<br>
Haste Buffs ... you bet<br>
Heals ... maybe<br>
Virtue ... are you fucking insane?<br>
I almost never use a chanter pet ... it is there pretty much ONLY to protect the chanter.  WHY THE HELL would you want to Virtue that?  call me cold, but I would rather the chanter DIE and get a rez than waste the time and manna on a virtue for a PET.<br>
